The paper focuses on deep learning for video understanding, specifically action recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture for spatial-temporal modeling, which involves training and optimizing the network, making it likely to fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses the Kinetics dataset, which is a large-scale human action recognition dataset, making it possible for the paper to fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new temporal Xception block, which is a type of convolutional neural network, making it possible for the paper to fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses extensive experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed framework, which involves training and optimizing the network, making it possible for the paper to fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
